Rating: 2
I having been making 'stoemp'for a long time using only one pot. I start off by frying pieces of bacon, then I add the leeks (and occasionally Belgian endive) and sweat them off, then I add the potatoes, carrots and water, etc. So you only need one pot, much easier.

Rating: 4
One of the easiest and best potato dishes I have found-underlining easy. Can make at least a day in advance and be done with it. As simple as it is, it is also unusual - the texture of carrots with the smoothness of the potatos. Leave carrots chunkier than the recipe says.

